20to%20the%20drugs%20usually%20used%20to%20treat%20them%2C%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fpublications%2Fi%2Fitem%2F9789240093461%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eantibiotics%20and%20antivirals%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EScientists%20must%20also%20constantly%20scan%20the%20horizon%20for%20the%20next%20potential%20problem.%20While%20this%20could%20come%20in%20any%20form%20of%20pathogen%2C%20certain%20groups%20are%20more%20likely%20than%20others%20to%20cause%20swift%20outbreaks%2C%20and%20that%20includes%20influenza%20viruses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20influenza%20virus%20is%20causing%20great%20concern%20right%20now%20and%20is%20teetering%20on%20the%20edge%20of%20being%20a%20serious%20problem%20in%202025.%20This%20is%20influenza%20A%20subtype%20H5N1%2C%20sometimes%20referred%20to%20as%20%E2%80%9Cbird%20flu%E2%80%9D.%20This%20virus%20is%20widely%20spread%20in%20both%20wild%20and%20domestic%20birds%2C%20such%20as%20poultry.%20Recently%2C%20it%20has%20also%20been%20infecting%20dairy%20cattle%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aphis.usda.gov%2Flivestock-poultry-disease%2Favian%2Favian-influenza%2Fhpai-livestock%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20several%20US%20states%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20found%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwwwnc.cdc.gov%2Feid%2Farticle%2F31%2F1%2F24-1266_article%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehorses%20in%20Mongolia%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20influenza%20cases%20start%20increasing%20in%20animals%20such%20as%20birds%2C%20there%20is%20always%20a%20worry%20that%20it%20could%20jump%20to%20humans.%20Indeed%2C%20bird%20flu%20can%20infect%20humans%20with%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdc.gov%2Fbird-flu%2Fsituation-summary%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E61%20cases%20in%20the%20US%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20year%20already%2C%20mostly%20resulting%20from%20farm%20workers%20coming%20into%20contact%20with%20infected%20cattle%20and%20people%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Favian-flu-virus-has-been-found-in-raw-milk-a-reminder-of-how-pasteurization-protects-health-245102%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edrinking%20raw%20milk%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECompared%20with%20only%20two%20cases%20in%20the%20Americas%20in%20the%20previous%20two%20years%2C%20this%20is%20quite%20a%20large%20increase.%20Coupling%20this%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fpublications%2Fm%2Fitem%2Fcumulative-number-of-confirmed-human-cases-for-avian-influenza-a(h5n1)-reported-to-who--2003-2024--27-september-2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E30%25%20mortality%20rate%20from%20human%20infections%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20bird%20flu%20is%20quickly%20jumping%20up%20the%20list%20of%20public%20health%20officials'%20priorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELuckily%2C%20H5N1%20bird%20flu%20doesn't%20seem%20to%20transmit%20from%20person%20to%20person%2C%20which%20greatly%20reduces%20its%20likelihood%20of%20causing%20a%20pandemic%20in%20humans.%20Influenza%20viruses%20have%20to%20attach%20to%20molecular%20structures%20called%20sialic%20receptors%20on%20the%20outside%20of%20cells%20in%20order%20to%20get%20inside%20and%20start%20replicating.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFlu%20viruses%20that%20are%20highly%20adapted%20to%20humans%20recognise%20these%20sialic%20receptors%20very%20well%2C%20making%20it%20easy%20for%20them%20to%20get%20inside%20our%20cells%2C%20which%20contributes%20to%20their%20spread%20between%20humans.%20Bird%20flu%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20is%20highly%20adapted%20to%20bird%20sialic%20receptors%20and%20has%20some%20mismatches%20when%20%E2%80%9Cbinding%E2%80%9D%20(attaching)%20to%20human%20ones.%20So%2C%20in%20its%20current%20form%2C%20H5N1%20can't%20easily%20spread%20in%20humans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20a%20recent%20study%20showed%20that%20a%20single%20mutation%20in%20the%20flu%20genome%20could%20make%20H5N1%20adept%20at%20spreading%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.science.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1126%2Fscience.adt0180%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efrom%20human%20to%20human%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20could%20jump-start%20a%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20this%20strain%20of%20bird%20flu%20makes%20that%20switch%20and%20can%20start%20transmitting%20between%20humans%2C%20governments%20must%20act%20quickly%20to%20control%20the%20spread.%20Centres%20for%20disease%20control%20around%20the%20world%20have%20drawn%20up%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ecdc.europa.eu%2Fen%2Favian-influenza-humans%2Fcountry-preparedness-plans-avian-influenza-humans%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epandemic%20preparedness%20plans%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20bird%20flu%20and%20other%20diseases%20that%20are%20on%20the%20horizon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20the%20UK%20has%20bought%205%20million%20doses%20of%20H5%20vaccine%20that%20can%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gov.uk%2Fgovernment%2Fnews%2Fuk-secures-h5-influenza-vaccine-to-boost-pandemic-preparedness%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprotect%20against%20bird%20flu%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20preparation%20for%20that%20risk%20in%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20without%20the%20potential%20ability%20to%20spread%20between%20humans%2C%20bird%20flu%20is%20likely%20to%20affect%20animal%20health%20even%20more%20in%202025.%20This%20not%20only%20has%20large%20animal%20welfare%20implications%20but%20also%20the%20potential%20to%20disrupt%20food%20supply%20and%20have%20economic%20effects%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Cows%20on%20a%20dairy%20farm.%5C%22%20sizes%3D%5C%22(min-width%3A%201466px)%20754px%2C%20(max-width%3A%20599px)%20100vw%2C%20(min-width%3A%