%20music.%20I%20wanted%20to%20dismiss%20it%20as%20any%20other%20insignificant%20day.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI'd%20get%20together%20with%20my%20family%20and%20try%20to%20pretend%20I%20was%20happy%20to%20be%20there%2C%20but%20I%20felt%20guilty%20for%20pretending%20and%20resentful%20of%20having%20to.%20Yet%20I%20didn't%20think%20not%20pretending%20was%20an%20option.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fif-youre-grieving-this-holiday-season-try-screaming-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ething%20about%20grief%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20though%2C%20is%20that%20with%20each%20year%2C%20the%20tide%20rose%2C%20washed%20away%20more%20grit%2C%20and%20left%20me%20softer.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f5621174-8668-43e4-bce0-978e2fc68680%5C%22%3EI%20had%20to%20find%20beauty%20in%20things%20again%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFrom%20the%20spring%20of%202019%20through%20the%20spring%20of%202020%2C%20I%20spent%20a%20year%20living%20in%20Denver.%20I%20needed%20to%20change%20my%20surroundings%20%E2%80%94%20and%20make%20a%20change%20that%20was%20in%20my%20control%20%E2%80%94%20to%20teach%20my%20brain%20that%20there%20could%20be%20beauty%20in%20newness.%20I%20needed%20to%20learn%20what%20the%20newness%20would%20make%20of%20me.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20I%20returned%20to%20Michigan%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20I%20returned%20as%20someone%20who%20had%20made%20new%20memories%20in%20a%20new%20place.%20It%20helped%20me%20accept%20that%20things%20could%20look%20different%20and%20still%20be%20good.%20The%20holidays%20could%20still%20be%20special%20if%20I%20wanted%20them%20to%20be.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDuring%20the%20Christmas%20of%202020%2C%20my%20sister%20and%20her%20family%20had%20COVID-19%2C%20so%20I%20stood%20outside%20their%20window%20in%20the%20snow%20for%2015%20minutes%20before%20going%20back%20to%20my%20apartment%20alone.%20I%20noticed%2C%20with%20sad%20poignancy%2C%20how%20much%20I%20wanted%20to%20be%20inside%20with%20her%2C%20my%20brother-in-law%2C%20my%20nephews%2C%20and%20my%20dad.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202021%2C%20I%20met%20my%20now%20wife%2C%20and%20I%20had%20the%20delicious%20instinct%20to%20make%20things%20special%20together.%20To%20create%20our%20own%20traditions.%20She%20prioritizes%20fun%2C%20and%20it%20rubbed%20off%20on%20me.%20I%20came%20to%20love%20taking%20part%20in%20her%20family's%20traditions%2C%20too.%20It%20became%20clear%20that%20there%20was%20so%20much%20celebration%20to%20go%20around%2C%20no%20matter%20what%20it%20looked%20like.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224df31cfa-e23d-4381-a11f-1b5eb2184e3a%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20look%20forward%20to%20the%20holidays%20now%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20year%20will%20be%20the%20seventh%20Christmas%20without%20my%20mother%2C%20and%20I%20look%20forward%20to%20the%20holiday%20now.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20wife%20and%20I%20put%20up%20our%20tree%20on%20November%203rd.%20To%20me%2C%20Christmas%20symbolizes%20coziness%2C%20a%20focus%20on%20joy%2C%20an%20excuse%20for%20good%20food%20and%20extra%20sugar%20and%20sitting%20around%20a%20table%20with%20people%20I%20love.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20there%20are%20traditions%2C%20new%20and%20old%2C%20that%20I%20cherish%2C%20it's%20less%20about%20the%20specifics%20and%20more%20about%20the%20%3Cem%3Efeeling%3C%2Fem%3E.%20And%2C%20grief%20is%20a%20part%20of%20that%20feeling.%20It's%20just%20not%20such%20a%20sharp%20ache%20anymore%20%E2%80%94%20more%20like%20a%20familiar%20smell%20that%20reminds%20me%20of%20a%20warm%20and%20nostalgic%20childhood%20memory.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHoliday%20grief%20(and%20any%20grief%2C%20for%20that%20matter)%20isn't%20a%20thing%20to%20be%20conquered%20and%20moved%20on%20from%2C%20but%20a%20thing