sinsider.com%2Fstates-where-middle-class-income-earners-pay-most-taxes-income-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emiddle-class%20camp%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20at%20Grandpa's%2C%20where%20they%20had%20to%20face%20horrors%20like%20having%20a%20fan%20instead%20of%20air%20conditioning.%20I%20approach%20the%20difference%20between%20my%20upbringing%20and%20theirs%20with%20humor%2C%20but%20the%20truth%20is%20no%20one%20imagines%20raising%20kids%20in%20an%20economic%20situation%20that's%20so%20vastly%20different%20from%20how%20they%20were%20raised.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e7bc14b2-24b8-4fa1-ae34-8c94ccb43198%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20want%20my%20kids%20to%20learn%20to%20prioritize%20financial%20decisions%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20book%20that's%20helped%20me%20greatly%20is%20%26quot%3BThe%20Opposite%20of%20Spoiled%26quot%3B%20by%20Ron%20Lieber.%20He%20talks%20about%20the%20importance%20of%20giving%20kids%20allowance%2C%20because%20that%20allows%20them%20to%20make%20mistakes%20with%20small%20amounts%20of%20money.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20wife%20and%20I%20give%20the%20kids%20a%20modest%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffamily-budget-tips-teenagers-give-allowance-vacation-economy-inflation-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emonthly%20allowance%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20That%20means%20we%20don't%20have%20to%20talk%20with%20them%20about%20money%20every%20day%2C%20and%20they%20weigh%20up%20whether%20they%20really%20want%20something%2C%20like%20a%20new%20soccer%20ball.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt's%20important%20to%20me%20that%20the%20kids%20know%20that%20money%20isn't%20in%20endless%20supply.%20If%20they%20buy%20X%2C%20they%20might%20not%20have%20enough%20money%20to%20buy%20Y.%20Although%20I%20have%20substantial%20wealth%2C%20I%20still%20prioritize%20my%20financial%20decisions.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20example%2C%20I%20could%20fly%20private%2C%20but%20that%20would%20require%20me%20to%20work%20in%20a%20traditional%20job%20to%20have%20more%20income%20coming%20in.%20Yet%2C%20it's%20more%20important%20to%20me%20to%20be%20able%20to%20do%20the%20type%20of%20work%20I%20enjoy%2C%20comedy%2C%20which%20happens%20to%20pay%20less.%20I%20value%20professional%20flexibility%20more%20than%20the%20status%20of%20flying%20private%20or%20the%20joys%20of%20getting%20to%20skip%20TSA%2C%20so%20I%20prioritize%20that.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fc058f79-a125-4064-9b81-9064491e9d5a%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EFinancial%20security%20has%20let%20me%20chase%20my%20dream%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI've%20loved%20comedy%20since%20I%20first%20got%20onstage%20at%20Dartmouth%20College%20during%20grad%20school.%20My%20parents%20paid%20for%20college%2C%20but%20I%20had%20%2480%2C000%20in%20student%20loans%20for%20graduate%20school%20back%20in%201997.%20That%20financial%20reality%20meant%20that%20I%20had%20to%20take%20a%20traditional%20job%20in%20the%20tech%20world%20rather%20than%20chase%20my%20dream%20of%20being%20a%20comedian.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20working%20in%20tech%20for%20a%20few%20years%20and%20paying%20off%20my%20student%20loans%2C%20I%20quit%20to%20pursue%20comedy%20full%20time%20for%20two%20years.%20My%20standard%20of%20living%20was%20still%20good%20because%20I%20had%20a%20lot%20saved.%20But%20when%20I%20met%20my%20wife%20and%20knew%20we%20wanted%20kids%2C%20I%20returned%20to%20the%20tech%20world%20because%20I%20wanted%20more%20financial%20security%20than%20life%20as%20a%20standup%20comedian%20could%20give%20me.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWorking%20at%20Facebook%20ended%20up%20being%20a%20bigger%20home%20run%20than%20I%20could%20have%20ever%20imagined.%20I%20remember%20saying%20to%20my%20wife%2C%20%26quot%3BThis%20might%20be%20as%20big%20as%20MySpace%20one%20day.%26quot%3B%20I%20couldn't%20even%20imagine%20how%20bi